  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0bae\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc2\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0ba4\u0bc1 : \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0bae\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0bca\u0b9f\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0b9a\u0baa\u0bc8 \u0b92\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bc0\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bcd 6 \u0b86\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0ba4\u0bbf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Parliament convenes on Monday: Debate on the adjournment motion on the state of the country will be held on the 6th",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "Parliament will convene next week on April 4, 5 and 6, Parliamentary Secretary General Dammika Dasanayake said. The decision was taken at a meeting of the Parliamentary Business Committee chaired by Speaker Mahinda Yapa Abeywardena on Thursday.",
        "The time allotted for the 50 oral questions which have not been asked in Parliament for various reasons will be from 10.00 am to 3.30 pm on the forthcoming 4th.",
        "The Parliament will also convene at 10.00 am on July 05 and the Regulations under the Foreign Exchange Act No. 12 of 2017, Orders published in the Gazette No. 2270/59 and 2280/32 of the Sri Lanka Export Development Act No. 40 of 1979 will be imported under the Customs Ordinance. The Secretary-General said that the decision on the tax was to be implemented after discussion on the order under Section 08 of the Appropriation Act No. 07 of 2020.",
        "Also, 6 orders under the Special Commodities Act No. 48 of 2007, Regulations No. 2282/21 and No. 2282/22 prescribed under the Import and Export (Controls) Act No. 01 of 1969 and published in Gazette Notifications No. 2282/22 will be approved in the House after the day's discussion.",
        "Meanwhile, time has been allotted for questions to be asked to the Prime Minister on July 6 from 10.00 am to 10.30 am. Following this, the debate on the Opposition's adjournment motion on the current situation in the country will continue until 4.30 pm, the Secretary General said.",
        "Also, due to the current difficulties, it has been decided to conduct online committee meetings on days when the Parliament is not in session and to take necessary further steps for this."
      ],
